news.title: Ramgarh cantonment board serves notices to 400 buildings
news.para: Under administrative control of the Union defence ministry, the CBR, which is responsible for the upkeep of the garrison town, has taken cognizance to a letter written by former MLA Shankar Choudhary.

news.title: DDA says over 22,000 applicants registered for special housing scheme 2021
news.para: "A total of 22,179 applicants have registered themselves for the scheme, out of which payments of 12,253 applicants have been confirmed and the final figure is being reconciled with banks," a senior official said.

news.title: Jharkhand puts drone survey under 'Swamitva Yojna' on hold amid tribal protest
news.para: The scheme, launched in April 2020, aims to create digital records of immovable properties of rural residents with the use of modern technology. Villagers, following the survey, will be provided property ownership cards.

news.title: HC dismisses PIL against Vizag land pooling scheme
news.para: The court made it clear that Visakhapatnam Metropolitan Region Development Authority can pool lands from those who willingly gave consent but not from those who did not agree to the land pooling scheme.

news.title: Residential project launches up 26% in state: Gujarat RERA
news.para: According to estimates by developers at the Gihed Property Show which was inaugurated at Ahmedabad on Friday, there is at least a 15% increase in new home sales in affordable, premium and luxury residential schemes.

news.title: Ludhiana: Uncertainty over Atal apartments
news.para: Now applicants under Atal Apartment scheme are worried as they were hoping that LIT will organise the draw of flats after election results.

news.title: Vadodara: Decks cleared for Sahakarnagar housing scheme
news.para: No development was seen in the housing scheme that was being developed as an in situ housing project on the public-private partnership mode under the Pradhan Mantri Aavas Yojana.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board panel on need-based changes gets April deadline
news.para: On September 8, 2021, the CHB had formed a committee to regularise building violations in dwelling units on the Delhi pattern of one-time settlement. The decision was taken in the board of directors meeting under the chairmanship of Pal, the chairman of the CHB.

news.title: Maharashtra government to probe allocation of reserved plots to builders without nod
news.para: Shinde said that a probe would be launched by the state urban development department to check how the corporation failed to alert the state government, and it will be ensured that the corporation seeks an okay from the state for all future proposals.

news.title: DB Realty's partnership firm gets MCGM's nod to construct 4,000 tenements
news.para: "DBS Realty, a partnership firm in which D B Realty Ltd is a one-third partner, has received a Letter of Acceptance (LOA) from MCGM against online e-offer/online e-tender submitted by the firm," D B Realty said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: BMC attaches 24 properties of Mumbai Metro One worth over Rs 300 crore
news.para: Officials said Rs 220 crore was from properties in K (west) ward, while Rs 80 crore from K (east) ward. A tussle between Mumbai Metropolitan Region Development Authority (MMRDA) and Mumbai Metro One Pvt Ltd (MMOPL) as to who should pay up was leading to non-payment, said officials.

news.title: Supertech twin towers: Edifice Engineering allays residents' fears
news.para: The private company given charge of the demolition of the towers said that its representatives on Thursday met residents of ATS Greens Village and Supertech Emerald Court – where the uninhabited 32-storey twin towers Apex and Ceyane are located.

news.title: West Bengal extends stamp duty & circle rate sops for six months
news.para: The principal chief advisor to CM Amit Mitra later said there has been a 25% jump in revenue from July 2021 to March (first week) 2022, following the exemption on stamp duty and circle rate reduction.

news.title: Sobha's vice chairman and managing director J C Sharma resigns
news.para: ​In a regulatory filing, Sobha informed that Sharma, vide a letter dated March 11, "tendered his resignation for the position of Director, Vice Chairman, Managing Director and Key Managerial Personnel of the company with effect from 1st April 2022."

news.title: WeWork expects 2022 revenue to jump at least 30% on office space demand
news.para: The Softbank-backed firm said it expects full-year revenue between $3.35 billion and $3.5 billion, a 30%-36% rise from its 2021 revenue.
